<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>don’t sweat it • don’t sweat the small stuff</xh5><p> <i>don’t sweat it</i>—(U.S. sl.) don’t worry: <u>Don’t sweat it</u>! We’ve got plenty of time to get there before the show starts.</p><p> <div class="note">Note</div> The expression does not correlate in meaning with the phrase <b>no sweat</b>—(sl.) used to say that one can do smth. with no difficulty or problem: “Do you think you’ll be able to manage all those boxes yourself?” “Yeah, <u>no sweat</u>!”</p><p> <i>don’t sweat the small stuff</i>—(U.S. sl.) don’t worry about things that are not important: You may have heard the phrase <u>don’t sweat the small stuff</u>. The person that said that wasn’t selling his home.</p> </entry>
